# ================================================================
# GymPass Registration Portal - Environment Variables
# ================================================================
# This is a static HTML/JS app, so env handling is different.
# 
# Location: Place this as `.env` in registration-portal/ root
# Note: These are for DOCUMENTATION only. See "How to Use" below.

# ----------------------------------------------------------------
# Configuration Variables
# ----------------------------------------------------------------
# API Base URL - where the backend API is hosted
# Dev default: Uses same-origin detection or localhost:4000
# Prod: https://gympass.hu or https://api.gympass.hu
API_BASE_URL=

# Public base URL - for displaying gym URLs after registration
# Dev default: http://localhost:4000
# Prod: https://gympass.hu
PUBLIC_BASE_URL=

# Tenant base domain - for gym subdomains
# Dev default: gym.local
# Prod: gympass.hu
TENANT_BASE_DOMAIN=

# Protocol (http or https)
# Dev default: http
# Prod: https
PROTOCOL=

# Port (leave empty in prod for standard 443)
# Dev default: 4000
# Prod: (empty)
PORT=

# ----------------------------------------------------------------
# How to Use (Static HTML)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------
# Since this is static HTML/JS, environment variables work differently:
#
# ===== Option A: Runtime Injection (RECOMMENDED) =====
# Inject config via inline <script> in index.html before config.js loads:
#
# <head>
#   <script>
#     window.ENV = {
#       PUBLIC_BASE_URL: 'https://gympass.hu',
#       TENANT_BASE_DOMAIN: 'gympass.hu',
#       PROTOCOL: 'https',
#       PORT: '',
#     };
#   </script>
#   <script src="config.js"></script>
# </head>
#
# This can be done:
#   - Manually in index.html before deploying
#   - Via deployment script (sed/envsubst)
#   - Via server-side template (if served by backend)
#
# ===== Option B: Build-Time Replacement =====
# Use a tool like envsubst during build/deploy:
#
# envsubst < index.html.template > index.html
# 
# Then in your template file use: ${PUBLIC_BASE_URL}
#
# ===== Option C: Serve Behind Reverse Proxy (SIMPLEST) =====
# If registration portal is served from the same domain as backend:
#   - No configuration needed!
#   - config.js will auto-detect and use same-origin /api paths
#   - Example: https://gympass.hu/register â†’ uses relative /api calls
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------
# Development
# ----------------------------------------------------------------
# No configuration needed!
# - Open index.html directly in browser (uses localhost:4000)
# - Or serve via backend: http://localhost:4000/register
# - config.js uses safe dev defaults
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------
# Production Deployment Examples
# ----------------------------------------------------------------
# Example 1: Same-origin (recommended)
#   - Serve portal at: https://gympass.hu/register
#   - Reverse proxy /api/* to backend
#   - No env injection needed (auto-detects)
#
# Example 2: Runtime injection
#   - Add inline script to index.html during deployment
#   - Deploy to static hosting (Vercel/Netlify/S3)
#
# Example 3: Build-time replacement
#   - Use sed/envsubst in CI/CD:
#     sed -i "s|__API_BASE_URL__|$API_BASE_URL|g" index.html
#   - Requires marking placeholders in HTML

# ----------------------------------------------------------------
# Security Note
# ----------------------------------------------------------------
# No secrets should be in this portal!
# It's a public-facing registration form.
# All sensitive operations (Stripe checkout) happen on backend.
